1 - Compile and install Touchégg:
    https://code.google.com/p/touchegg/wiki/CompileSourceCode

2 - Configure your device:
    http://code.google.com/p/touchegg/wiki/ConfigureDevices

3 - Run Touchégg:
    $ touchegg

4 - Make a gesture, for example drag two fingers over your trackpad. If all
    works fine, the name of the gesture will appear.

5 - To use your own configuration edit ~/.touchegg/touchegg.conf or use the GUI.
